\date{2024-09-23}
\title{characterization of normal subgroups}
\taxon{proposition}
\author{rileyshahar}

\cite{aluffi-2009}{Aluffi}{Section II.7.6}
\import{macros01}

\p{A [subgroup](rs-009J) #{N} is [normal](rs-009K), i.e. the [kernel](rs-00A4)
of a map #{f}, if and only if it is closed under [conjugation](rs-009P). We
write #{N\unlhd G}.}

\p{Most authors take this latter condition as the definition of normal
subgroups.}
